Constructor for the interaction-class

Source: R/model.R
initialize-interaction-method.Rd

Constructor for the interaction-class

Usage

# S4 method for class 'interaction'
initialize(.Object, parameters = c(0, 0, 0, 0), sd = 1)

Arguments

.Object

Model to initialize

parameters

Numeric vector containing the values of the parameters of the model, namely \(a\), \(b\), \(c\), and \(d\) in this order. If left unspecified, the model will default to c(0, 0, 0, 0).

sd

Numeric defining the error around the deterministic part defined by the argument parameters. If left unspecified, will default to 1
